    <h1>Conditions of Use for the Online Portal EFynch</h1>
    <h2>GENERAL REMARKS ON HOW IT WORKS</h2>
    <p>Welcome to EFynch – a product of EFynch.Com (“EFynch.Com“).  The following Conditions of Use govern your use of this EFynch website/portal and EFynch via mobile application (collectively, “EFynch Portal”), an Electronic Product, whether to visit the site or register to become a “Designated User” of the EFynch Portal. <strong>If you visit the EFynch Portal, you accept these Conditions of Use</strong>.  These Conditions of Use, as amended from time to time, supplement any terms and conditions in any other agreement.</p>

    <p>EFynch.Com provides this EFynch Portal to Users, free of charge, to solicit bids from Service Professionals for their projects, including, but not limited to, electrical work, plumbing work, landscaping and yard work, hardscaping work, garbage removal, kitchen/bath renovations, roofing work, painting, and other minor and major projects. Users can upload project related information and descriptions for review and bidding by Service Professionals.  The EFynch Portal offers a platform on which Service Professionals can then submit bids and other information to the User to compare.  Service Professionals, pursuant to a separate license agreement, pay a license fee for the use of the EFynch Portal per project, which fee is based upon a percentage of the project value (“Service Professional license fee“).  Once the User selects a Service Professional, EFynch allows the Service Professional and User to easily exchange information regarding the project, including contract documents, drawings, change orders, invoicing, communication and other project documents.   The User does not pay the Service Professional upfront; rather, the following business day after the User and Service Professional enter into a contract for the project, the User escrows the contract amount with EFynch.Com and then directs EFynch.Com when to release funds to the Service Professional during the course of the project.  Users can then submit an assessment of the Service Professional and the Service Professionals can respond to the assessment via the EFynch Portal. EFynch.Com reserves the right to remove any assessments or comments that it deems, in its sole discretion and without recourse or liability to the Service Professional or User, to violate these terms.</p>

