    <h3>DISCLAIMERS DIRECT TO USERS</h3>
    <p>Service Professionals are not screened by EFynch.Com.   Service Professionals must register as a Designated User, to bid any Work and, as part of that process, each Service Professional must represent, acknowledge and affirm the following:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Licensing</strong>. Each Service Professional must acknowledge that it is properly licensed by the State or Local authorities, if applicable, to perform any Work for which it bids. Before accepting any bids, Users should confirm these licensing requirements with the applicable state and local licensing authorities.</li>
      <li><strong>Permits</strong>. Each Service Professional must also acknowledge that it will conform to any requirements regarding permitting and governmental approval <strong>required by the county or local authority in which the Work is being performed. We recommend you confirm these permitting and approval requirements before proceeding with your project. Some states and local authorities hold Users liable for failing to obtain proper permits and governmental approval for Work</strong>.</li>
      <li><strong>Subcontractors or Subcontractor</strong>.   Larger projects often require the use of subcontractors or other trades for specific types of Work. Each Service Professional must acknowledge that it will only subcontract with individuals or companies properly licensed by the State or Local authorities, if applicable, to perform any portion of the Work.  Users should confirm these licensing requirements with the applicable State and Local licensing authorities to verify that all the subcontractors doing Work carry the appropriate licensing.  EFynch.Com cannot verify the licensing status of Service Professionals or subcontractors and relies on the representation of the Service Professionals. </li>
      <li><strong>State Business Filings</strong> – If a Service Professional is a corporation or limited liability company, that Service Professional must acknowledge that it is in good standing in the state in which it is located.  Users should check with the state body governing corporations to confirm this information.</li>
      <li><strong>Criminal Records Search</strong>.  Each Service Professional must also swear that he or she has not been convicted of a serious crime, felony or misdemeanor other than minor traffic violations. EFynch.Com, however, does not perform criminal records searches on Service Professionals.   Users may be able to obtain criminal records searches from third party vendors.  Furthermore, Users may be able to check the Sex Offender Registry of the state in which the Service Professional resides or is in business. EFynch.Com does not run sex offender searches in any states.   Civil and criminal records may also be publicly available in the state in which the Service Professional resides or is in business.</li>
      <li><strong>Qualifications</strong>.  EFynch.Com will take certain steps to bar any Service Professional from the use of the EFynch Portal if EFynch.Com is informed of i) a Service Professional’s false or inaccurate representation, acknowledgment or affirmation related to becoming a Designated User or in connection with the use of the EFynch Portal; or ii) any failure to complete the Work pursuant to industry standards and applicable laws. EFynch.Com makes no guarantees or representations regarding the skills or representations of any Service Professional or the quality of the job that he or she may perform. <strong>EFynch.Com does not endorse, solicit or recommend the services of any Service Professional</strong>. The User is solely responsible to investigate and assess a Service Professional‘s qualifications. EFynch.Com does not negotiate or get involved in the selection or contracting of any Service Professional. The User is solely responsible for selecting and entering into a direct contract or otherwise reach an agreement with a Service Professional. EFynch.Com does not guarantee or warrant any Service Professional‘s performance of the Work. EFynch.Com is not an agent of any Service Professional. Use of the EFynch Portal to obtain bids from Service Professionals or to upload construction documents, including contracts, does not create any contractual relationship between the User and EFynch.Com for the performance of the Work.  The User’s rights are governed by the contractual relationship with the Service Professional selected to perform the Work, and the User agrees that any dispute regarding the performance of the Work will rest solely with the Service Professional and not with EFynch.Com.  You agree that EFynch.Com is not responsible for the accessibility or unavailability of any Service Professional or for your interactions and dealings with any Service Professional, waive the right to bring or assert any claim against EFynch.Com relating to any interactions or dealings with any Service Professional, and release EFynch.Com from any and all liability for or relating to any interactions or dealings with Service Professionals or the Work.</li>
      <li>EFynch.Com is not a contractor and does not provide, arrange for, offer or bid on any Work.  EFynch.Com also will not and does not negotiate or offer to negotiate any contract for any Work.   EFynch.Com is not a contractor, subcontractor, tradesman, salesperson or estimator with respect to any Work.   EFynch.Com provides the EFynch Portal as project management software and bidding solution to Users and Service Professionals.   EFynch.Com is not responsible for the accuracy of the information or Content uploaded by Users or Service Professionals, which are solely responsible for ensuring the accuracy of the information.</li>
    </ul>
