    <h3>PAYMENT FOR WORK – DEPOSIT OF CONTRACT FUNDS WITH EFYNCH.COM</h3>
    <p>The following business day after User and the Service Professional have fully negotiated and executed a written contract for the Work, the User shall then deposit the contract price for the Work with EFynch.Com.  EFynch.Com shall hold the deposit in trust for the User for the payment of the Work.   EFynch.Com shall promptly and no later than seven (7) days from receipt of the same deposit the money in an account that is maintained by EFynch.Com in a financial institution that has one or more branch locations in the State in which the Work is performed and whose deposits are insured by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation.   Such account need not be an interest bearing checking or saving account or any combination thereof.  EFynch.Com shall maintain the money in the account until:</p>
    <ul>
      <ol>Directed by the User to pay the Service Professional any whole or part thereof for the Work.</ol>
      <ol>Directed by the User to return the contract price to the User due to a cancellation of the Work, in which case, the contract price shall be returned less any credit card or bank processing fees incurred by EFynch.Com.  EFynch.Com shall also be entitled to withhold that portion of the Service Professional’s License Fee in proportion to the amount paid to the Service Professional for the Work performed.</ol>
      <ol>Directed by the User to return the contract price to the User due to a good-faith dispute regarding the performance of the Service Professional relative to any part of the Work, in which case, the contract price shall be returned less any credit card or bank processing fees incurred by EFynch.Com and EFynch.Com shall retain and hold in trust the Service Professional’s Licensing Fee to be held pending a resolution or settlement of the dispute between Service Professional and the User.  EFynch.Com shall be entitled to that portion of the Service Professional’s License Fee in proportion to the amount paid to the Service Professional  as part of any resolution or settlement, including any judgment.</ol>
      <ol>A Court directs EFynch.Com to distribute the money in a different manner.
        <p>Service Professional and User agree that EFynch.Com shall have the right to offset from any payment to the Service Professional any amounts due by Service Professional to EFynch.Com for Service Professional’s use of the EFynch Portal.</p>
        <p>In the event of any dispute or litigation between User and Service Professional regarding the contract price held by EFynch.Com, User and Service Professional agree that EFynch.Com shall have the option to pay the money into a Court and neither User nor Service Professional has any further right, claim, demand or action against EFynch.Com related to the deposit.  If EFynch.Com elects to pay the money to the User in lieu of the Court, Service Professional has no right, claim, demand or action against EFynch.Com related to the deposit.  Any action for non-payment related to the Work shall rest solely between User and Service Professional, and User and Service Professional each agree to indemnify and defend EFynch.Com from any claim by the other related to the payment of the Work.  In the event EFynch.Com pays the deposit into a court vis-à-vis a interpleader or other action, EFynch.Com shall have the right to deduct from the deposit its filing fees, court costs, service of process fees and attorneys’ fees, provided the amount does not exceed the amount of the deposit.   The forgoing fees, as well as any other fees due EFynch.Com hereunder, may be deducted by EFynch.Com before the money is paid into the Court.   And, if the amount deducted is less than the actual fees incurred by EFynch.Com in that action, then the User and Service Professional agree that the balance may be deducted prior to the payment of the deposit to the User or Service Professional as directed by the Court, as the case may be.</p>
      </ol>
    </ul>
